Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a
#medium pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{1}(cut into bite-size pieces) into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you
> can get started on them now!

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @everything bagel seasoning{1%tablespoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain, then return pasta to pot.

While pasta cooks, in pan used for panko, whisk together @cream sauce base{4%ounce}
and @water{1%cup} over medium heat. Bring to a simmer.

Add @cream cheese{6%tablespoon}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, and
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}. Cook, whisking, until cream cheese is fully
incorporated and sauce is smooth, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Whisk in three-quarters of the @cheddar cheese{2%cup} and
@butter{1%tablespoon} until melted and smooth. Taste and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} if desired.

Transfer cheese sauce to pot with drained cavatappi; stir to combine.

Coat an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} with @nonstick cooking spray{}. Transfer mac
'n' cheese to prepared #baking dish{}.

Top with remaining cheddar and bake on middle rack until browned,
~{12-15%minutes}. Let rest ~{5%minutes} before serving.

While mac 'n' cheese bakes, halve @jalapeño{1}(halved lengthwise, ribs and seeds
removed) lengthwise, removing ribs and seeds for less heat; thinly slice crosswise
into half-moons. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces) into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

In a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine jalapeño, @white wine vinegar{1%teaspoon},
@sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

> Save remaining vinegar for another use.

Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle,
stirring occasionally.

Serve broccoli, mac 'n' cheese, toasted panko, tomato, and pickled jalapeño
family style and let everyone build their own plate.